hands_on_practices.problem:
Consider two continuous-time signals, $x(t)$ and $h(t)$, defined for all real numbers $t$. The signal $x(t)$ is a triangular pulse defined by the piecewise function:
$$
x(t) = \begin{cases}
1 + t  \text{for } -1 \le t  0 \\
1 - t  \text{for } 0 \le t \le 1 \\
0  \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
$$
The signal $h(t)$ is the unit step function, defined as:
$$
h(t) = \begin{cases}
1  \text{for } t \ge 0 \\
0  \text{for } t  0
\end{cases}
$$
Let the signal $y(t)$ be the result of the convolution of $x(t)$ with $h(t)$, denoted as $y(t) = x(t) * h(t)$. Determine the complete analytical expression for $y(t)$ for all real values of $t$.
